00:35:05,896 --> 00:35:07,814
Careful of the step.

402
00:35:12,027 --> 00:35:14,529
That's good. I got it. I got it.

403
00:35:15,489 --> 00:35:17,824
The first song, Country Strong, right?

404
00:35:17,908 --> 00:35:18,950
Yes.

405
00:35:19,034 --> 00:35:21,452
Are you all right?

406
00:36:39,990 --> 00:36:42,492
Now, ladies and gentlemen,

407
00:36:42,576 --> 00:36:46,871
the star of tonight's show,
six-time Grammy winner,

408
00:36:46,955 --> 00:36:51,584
the belle of Bristol,
our very own Kelly Canter.

409
00:37:13,107 --> 00:37:16,150
Hold on one second. Wait, wait, wait, wait.

410
00:37:20,572 --> 00:37:22,365
Sorry. I just...

411
00:37:25,119 --> 00:37:26,994
Thank you so much.

412
00:37:33,335 --> 00:37:37,588
You just cannot understand
what this means to me. Thank you.

413
00:37:38,674 --> 00:37:40,299
We love you!

414
00:37:51,562 --> 00:37:55,648
I was just in my dressing room,

415
00:37:55,732 --> 00:37:57,358
and I was looking out the window,

416
00:37:57,443 --> 00:38:01,195
and I was looking up at the big, bright sky,

417
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:04,031
and there are so many stars.

418
00:38:04,116 --> 00:38:05,700
And I thought,

419
00:38:07,786 --> 00:38:12,206
"Man, it looks like they would take
such good care of you."

420
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:16,294
Do you know what I mean?

421
00:38:18,046 --> 00:38:20,047
Come on, baby, come on. Don't do this.

422
00:38:20,132 --> 00:38:24,051
I never lived on a star,
but it sure looks like fun.

423
00:38:32,102 --> 00:38:34,770
Hey, what did y'all think of Beau?

424
00:38:36,482 --> 00:38:38,399
Wasn't he great?

425
00:38:38,484 --> 00:38:40,985
Let's go. Come on, come on, play!

426
00:38:44,490 --> 00:38:46,491
Come on, baby, come on. Sing!

427
00:38:47,659 --> 00:38:50,328
